{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:psalms.49",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 49,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 49 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.49.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:1",
      "text": "Hear this, all peoples! Give ear, all inhabitants of the world,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.49.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:2",
      "text": "both low and high, rich and poor together!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.49.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:3",
      "text": "My mouth shall speak wisdom; the meditation of my heart shall be understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.49.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:4",
      "text": "I will incline my ear to a proverb; I will solve my riddle to the music of the lyre.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.49.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:5",
      "text": "Why should I fear in times of trouble, when the iniquity of my persecutors surrounds me,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.49.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:6",
      "text": "men who trust in their wealth and boast of the abundance of their riches?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.49.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:7",
      "text": "Truly no man can ransom himself, or give to God the price of his life,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.49.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:8",
      "text": "for the ransom of his life is costly, and can never suffice,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.49.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:9",
      "text": "that he should continue to live on for ever, and never see the Pit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.49.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:10",
      "text": "Yea, he shall see that even the wise die, the fool and the stupid alike must perish and leave their wealth to others.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.49.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:11",
      "text": "Their graves are their homes for ever, their dwelling places to all generations, though they named lands their own.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.49.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:12",
      "text": "Man cannot abide in his pomp, he is like the beasts that perish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.49.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:13",
      "text": "This is the fate of those who have foolish confidence, the end of those who are pleased with their portion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.49.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:14",
      "text": "Like sheep they are appointed for Sheol; Death shall be their shepherd; straight to the grave they descend, and their form shall waste away; Sheol shall be their home.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.49.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:15",
      "text": "But God will ransom my soul from the power of Sheol, for he will receive me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.49.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:16",
      "text": "Be not afraid when one becomes rich, when the glory of his house increases.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.49.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:17",
      "text": "For when he dies he will carry nothing away; his glory will not go down after him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.49.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:18",
      "text": "Though, while he lives, he counts himself happy, and though a man gets praise when he does well for himself,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.49.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:19",
      "text": "he will go to the generation of his fathers, who will never more see the light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.49.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:20",
      "text": "Man cannot abide in his pomp, he is like the beasts that perish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
